api_data.heading: COVID Vaccine Trial Site Selection
api_data.title_text:
As Pfizer and BioNTech advance the nucleoside-modified messenger RNA (modRNA) candidate BNT162b2 against COVID-19, the Phase 2/3 trails aim to study upto 30,000 participants aged 18-85 years in the US.

Our study aims to prioritize and recommend trial sites/counties  having higher predicted attack rates and disease load over the next 6 weeks, to help maximize trial registrations.

html.heading: One model doesn't fit all; exploring COVID trends
para: With varied local policies and guidelines to tackle the virus, coupled with varied responses from the population to these policies, we observe diverse trends in the growth of cases across counties.
The chart on the right showcases  counties with respect to rise of cases from previous week and number of confirmed cases till 17th August.
Counties like NY & others on the north east had high cases in the recent past, but have stabilized, compared to few counties California where cases are on the rise.
html.footer: Click on any bubble to view its confirmed cases history since March.

html.heading: Prioritizing trial sites based on model outcomes
para: The map displays predictions from our 4th refresh for week of 31st August. The color scale here represents the expected attack rate across counties, and we clearly see few counties where AR is expected to be on the rise over the next 6 weeks which could translate to better clinical trial registrations.

html.heading: Exploring model outcomes
para: In addition to new cases, we also look at Attack Rate which is calculated as (100,000/county population) * (under-reporting multiplier) * (adult multiplier)
Comparing our predictions of 17th August with actual attack rate, we have classified counties into 4 different buckets :
High AR - High Error
High AR - Low Error
Low AR - High Error
Low AR - Low Error

Counties whose actual attack rates in differed from the predicted attack rates by less than 15% were classified as low error. Counties whose average attack rates were at least 100 were classified as high attack rate

html.heading: An Ensemble modelling approach
para: We have developed 3 different model constructs to be able to capture these diverse signals across counties.
ARIMAX - Traditional time-series forecasting model, with flexibility to add exogenous variables
Hyper Feature Engineered Prediction Model - Prediction approach, trained on 8+ Million features
ML Quintile Model - Regression based prediction approach
In the latest release, we observe that ARIMAX provides the best estimates for 51 counties, followed by ML Quintile Model for 29 and Hyper Feature Engineered for 11
html.footer: Toggle between charts to see contribution of different models across previous refreshes

html.heading: Benchmarking model performance
para: Through real world validation of our models i.e. comparing what was predicted earlier v/s what is happening in actual, we observe good model performance for most counties. In addition, Pfizer's forecast models show positive signs in comparison with Columbia University's benchmark models. With improvements to few outlier counties with bad error rates, we would be able to improve our model performance further

html.heading: Exploring new data sources to capture policy changes and human behavior
para: With the objective of forecasting # of new COVID cases at the county level, we're capturing various leading and lagging indicators to estiamte the impact of the virus.
With a mix of IHME state models data, Mobility data, Voting data and socio-economic data from RWJ, we have over 400+ features used to train our models.
